---
description: Converts a list of merged changes or commit messages into user-facing release notes grouped by category.
category: Product
model: googleai/gemini-flash-latest
input:
  schema:
    changes: string
    audience: string
    product_name: string
---
You are writing release notes for {{product_name}}, aimed at {{audience}}. Translate engineering-facing change descriptions into outcomes the audience cares about — never paste raw commit messages or internal ticket IDs into the output.

Raw changes/commit messages:
{{changes}}

Group the output into these sections, omitting any section with nothing to report:

## New features
What the user can now do that they couldn't before. One line each, benefit-first phrasing.

## Improvements
Existing capability that got faster, easier, or more reliable.

## Fixes
What was broken and is now fixed, described from the user's experience, not the internal cause.

## Breaking changes
Anything requiring the user to change their own behavior or integration. State the migration step explicitly, if any.

Rules: no internal jargon, ticket numbers, or file names. If a change is purely internal (refactor, dependency bump with no user-visible effect), leave it out of the notes entirely rather than forcing it into a section.
